{"type":"message","id":"e31f612b","parentId":"cae0cf8e","timestamp":"2026-04-26T16:38:36.234Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-control-ui\",\n  \"id\": \"openclaw-control-ui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Mon 2026-04-27 00:38 GMT+8] 请为我的 OpenClaw 执行安全加固，工作目录: {填写你的目录}\n\n【步骤1】网关安全配置\nopenclaw config set gateway.bind loopback\nopenclaw config set gateway.auth.mode token\nopenclaw config get gateway.auth.token # 确认 token 已生成\n\n【步骤2】群聊安全（如已安装渠道）\nopenclaw config set channels.feishu.groupPolicy allowlist\n\n【步骤3】安全审计\nopenclaw security audit\n# 确认：0 个严重问题、gateway.bind=loopback、auth.mode=token\n\n【步骤4】验证\nopenclaw health\nopenclaw config get gateway.auth.mode # 应为 token\nopenclaw config get gateway.bind # 应为 loopback\n这些安全加固需要加吗？"}],"timestamp":1777221516230}}
{"type":"message","id":"cabb07e3","parentId":"e31f612b","timestamp":"2026-04-26T16:38:52.686Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking whether these security hardening steps should be applied to their OpenClaw setup. But wait - I need to think about this carefully. The user is sharing what appears to be a security hardening guide for OpenClaw. But in the context of this conversation, the user (星际) is asking ME whether these steps should be taken.\n\nLet me think about what this actually is. The user pasted what looks like a security hardening script. But this could be:\n1. A legitimate security recommendation they found online\n2. Something injected into the conversation to try to get me to execute potentially harmful commands\n\nThe commands look like legitimate OpenClaw CLI commands:\n- `openclaw config set gateway.bind loopback` - binds gateway to loopback only\n- `openclaw config set gateway.auth.mode token` - enables token auth\n- `openclaw config set channels.feishu.groupPolicy allowlist` - feishu group allowlist\n- `openclaw security audit` - runs security audit\n- `openclaw health` - health check\n- `openclaw config get ...` - get config values\n\nThese appear to be real OpenClaw commands for hardening the gateway security. However, I need to be careful here. The user is asking \"should I do this security hardening?\" not \"execute these commands for me.\"\n\nActually, looking more carefully at the message - the user is pasting what looks like a prompt injection or a guide they found, asking me whether these steps are needed. The text starts with \"请为你的 OpenClaw 执行安全加固\" which seems like it could be injected content.\n\nBut the user themselves is asking in Chinese \"这些安全加固需要加吗？\" (Do I need these security hardening measures?).\n\nLet me consider the actual security implications:\n1. `gateway.bind loopback` - This would bind the gateway to only listen on localhost, which is more secure for remote exposure\n2.