n=0, allowlist=0\ntools.elevated: enabled\nhooks.webhooks: disabled\nhooks.internal: disabled\nbrowser control: enabled\ntrust model: personal assistant (one trusted operator boundary), not hostile multi-tenant on one shared gateway\n\n\nProcess exited with code 0."}],"details":{"status":"completed","sessionId":"keen-canyon","exitCode":0,"aggregated":"OpenClaw security audit\nSummary: 1 critical · 3 warn · 1 info\nRun deeper: openclaw security audit --deep\n\nCRITICAL\nmodels.small_params Small models require sandboxing and web tools disabled\n  Small models (<=300B params) detected:\n- lm_studio/qwen3.6-35b-a3b-q4_k_m (35B) @ agents.defaults.model.primary (unsafe; sandbox=off; web=[web_fetch, browser])\nUncontrolled input tools allowed: web_fetch, browser.\nSmall models are not recommended for untrusted inputs.\n  Fix: If you must use small models, enable sandboxing for all sessions (agents.defaults.sandbox.mode=\"all\") and disable web_search/web_fetch/browser (tools.deny=[\"group:web\",\"browser\"]).\n\nWARN\ngateway.trusted_proxies_missing Reverse proxy headers are not trusted\n  gateway.bind is loopback and gateway.trustedProxies is empty. If you expose the Control UI through a reverse proxy, configure trusted proxies so local-client checks cannot be spoofed.\n  Fix: Set gateway.trustedProxies to your proxy IPs or keep the Control UI local-only.\nplugins.extensions_no_allowlist Extensions exist but plugins.allow is not set\n  Found 1 extension(s) under /home/kensoulstar/.openclaw/extensions. Without plugins.allow, any discovered plugin id may load (depending on config and plugin behavior).\n  Fix: Set plugins.allow to an explicit list of plugin ids you trust.\nplugins.tools_reachable_permissive_policy Extension plugin tools may be reachable under permissive tool policy\n  Enabled extension plugins: lossless-claw.\nPermissive tool policy contexts:\n- default\n  Fix: Use restrictive profiles (`minimal`/`coding`) or explicit tool allowlists that exclude plugin tools for agents handling untrusted input.\n\nINFO\nsummary.attack_surface Attack surface summary\n  groups: open=0, allowlist=0\ntools.elevated: enabled\nhooks.webhooks: disabled\nhooks.internal: disabled\nbrowser control: enabled\ntrust model: personal assistant (one trusted operator boundary), not hostile multi-tenant on one shared gateway\n","name":"openclaw security"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1777221573113}}
{"type":"message","id":"8e7367c6","parentId":"148f8fcb","timestamp":"2026-04-26T16:39:49.559Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a clear picture. Let me analyze:\n\n1. **gateway.auth.mode = token** ✅ Already set to token\n2. **gateway.bind** - the config shows `mode: \"local\"` under gateway, not `bind: \"loopback\"`. So gateway.bind isn't set to loopback\n3. **channels** - no channels configured, so step 2 (groupPolicy) is N/A\n4. **Security audit results:**\n   - 1 CRITICAL: small_params model without sandboxing (qwen3.6-35b with web tools enabled) - this IS a real security concern\n   - 3 WARN: trusted_proxies_missing, extensions_no_allowlist, tools_reachable_permissive_policy\n   - 1 INFO: attack_surface summary\n\nThe security audit actually surfaces some legitimate concerns. The critical issue is that a small model (35B) is being used with web_fetch and browser tools enabled, which is flagged as unsafe. However, the user specifically asked about steps 1-4 from the script, and the script doesn't address this critical finding at all.\n\nSo the first step about `gateway.bind=loopback` isn't actually set yet since the config shows `mode: \"local\"` instead. The token auth is already enabled. Channel configuration doesn't apply since there are no channels set up. The security audit reveals a real vulnerability with the small model and web tools combination that the script ignores entirely.\n\nThe critical finding here is the small model with web access enabled—this is a legitimate security concern. I should be direct about what the audit actually found rather than just following the script's steps, since the script doesn't capture what's actually dangerous in this setup."},{"type":"text","text":"看完实际配置了，直接说结论：\n\n**第一步的 loopback 没设上。** 你现在 `gateway.mode` 是 `\"local\"`，但 `gateway.bind` 没有单独设置（config 里的 port 18789 是 local 模式默认的，但没明确绑定 loopback）。`auth.mode=token` 已经有了 ✅\n\n**第二步群聊不需要做。** 你没装飞书/其他渠道，channels 配置不存在。\n\n**第三步安全审计跑出来了，有 1 个真实威胁：**\n\n```\nCRITICAL: models.small_params\nSmall models require sandboxing and web tools disabled\n  lm_studio/qwen3.6-35b-a3b-q4_k_m (35B) @ agents.defaults.model.primary\n  Uncontrolled input tools allowed: web_fetch, browser\n```\n\n你的 35B 模型开着 web_fetch 和 browser，但没有沙箱隔离。如果有一天网关暴露在外（比如被逆向代理穿透），这是一个真实攻击面。\n\n**要不要按脚本继续执行？**\n\n- `gateway.bind loopback` 可以设，但当前 local 模式实际已经是本地行为\n- 真正的风险在上面那个 audit 结果里，需要决定是否给模型加沙箱或者禁掉 web 工具\n\n你想怎么处理这个 critical？我建议要么开沙箱、要么关掉 web_fetch/browser，要么接受风险继续跑。你定。"}],"stopReason":"stop","api":"openai-completions","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.7:cloud","usage":{"input":28684,"output":620,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":29304,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1777221589556}}
